sec.p:
The reconstruction reveals a southward mean ITCZ position during the early MWP and the CWP. Spectral analysis indicates significant ∼1,000-, ∼400-, 130- to 140-, and ∼60-y cycles in the ITCZ SI record (
  
   SI Appendix, Fig. S15
  ). Further ensemble empirical mode decomposition analysis suggests that these cycles contribute 6%, 54%, 28%, and 8%, respectively, of ITCZ variance during the last 2,000 y (
  
   SI Appendix, Fig. S16
  ). The 130- to 140- and ∼60-y cycles are significant throughout the entire ITCZ SI reconstruction (
  
   SI Appendix, Fig. S17
  ).
